      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That \"doing my best\" thing... it doesn't feel like enough anymore. It feels like I'm just teaching them how to be unhappy, or how to deal with a person who can't even keep it together. It's like I'm a broken part of their childhood that they'll never be able to fix. If I keep going like this, I'm just going to keep poisoning everything they try to build for themselves. It feels like the only way to actually stop the damage would be to just... not be there. To give them a chance to breathe without my heaviness around.",
